Meet <b>Amy</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Amy's carefully designed home is the perfect place to relax after a day by the lake. Since May 19, 2006, she has happily resided at <a href='/home/?user=purdumamy030872'>94230 Bluebird Street</a> in Lakeview, a great neighborhood for a nature lover like her. <br><br>Amy is so excited it's spring and can't wait for summer! Warm weather is her favorite, and it means she'll get to hang out by the pool all the time. With favorite colors light blue, pink, and yellow, she is ready to debut her spring wardrobe full of light pastel colors. She will also have more time to go hiking, which she finds both relaxing and challenging.<br><br>Recently, she has been readying her yard sale for what she is sure will be a busy season. More people than usual are out perusing the various items their neighbors are selling, and now that the weather is nice, she plans to offer the best selection on her block. Yard sales are fun for her because she loves meeting people and talking about her favorite interests&mdash;books and computers. <br><br>So, stop by her home and check out all the cool stuff she's got! Thanks for being a good citizen, Amy, and congrats on being named Citizen of the Week!</div>
